# Hub system-context (not memory-bank)

The hub uses **`system-context/`** for cross-repo narrative. Code repos keep **`memory-bank/`** for experiments.

## Read tiers

| When | Read |
|------|------|
| Every hub-orchestrated task | `system-context/activeContext.md`, `system-context/progress.md` |
| Cross-repo structure, onboarding, “how do repos fit?” | `system-context/architecture.md` |
| Registry or missing workspace folder | `registry/projects.yaml` |
| Large hub-only milestone or user says **update system context** | All files under `system-context/` |

Do **not** mirror per-environment RL logs in the hub; write those to the active code repo’s `memory-bank/`.

## Write tiers

After hub-level changes (registry, workspace file, new repo wired in):

- Update `system-context/activeContext.md` and `system-context/progress.md`
- Update `system-context/architecture.md` when structure or repo count changes
